01:54.388 --> 01:58.887
[Male Narrating] Meet Charlie--
helpful dad, upstanding citizen...

01:58.897 --> 02:04.076
and an 18-year veteran of the greatest
law enforcement agency in the land.

02:04.086 --> 02:07.911
- [Whistling]
- the Rhode Island State Police.

02:12.087 --> 02:16.395
That's Charlie's home--
modest, like the man.

02:16.471 --> 02:18.858
Even though he lived
on the water,

02:18.868 --> 02:21.267
Charlie wasn't
much of a swimmer...

02:21.277 --> 02:24.403
which will come into play
a little later in our story.

02:24.413 --> 02:27.021
But I'm getting way ahead
of myself.

02:27.031 --> 02:32.758
You know, maybe it's best if we just
go back and begin at the beginning.

02:32.768 --> 02:36.595
As a young man, Charlie had the world
by its bootstraps.

02:36.605 --> 02:39.061
He was the best young trooper
on the force...

02:39.071 --> 02:42.418
and was dating the prettiest
and smartest gal in town.

02:42.428 --> 02:45.688
Her name was Layla,
just like the melody.

02:45.698 --> 02:47.866
Mmm, Charlie.

02:47.933 --> 02:50.993
You have no idea
how much I love you.

02:53.824 --> 02:56.673
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

02:56.740 --> 03:00.061
- Well, will you stay
with me no matter what?

03:00.071 --> 03:02.071
Of course, Charlie.

03:03.398 --> 03:06.908
Well, what if I had to move to the
Arctic, and you could never come home,

03:06.918 --> 03:09.143
and you had to eat whale blubber
for the rest of your life?

03:09.153 --> 03:13.233
- Would you still stay with me?
- Yeah, I'd stay.

03:15.944 --> 03:20.097
- But I hope that never happens.
- Yeah, me too.

03:20.164 --> 03:22.164
[Cheering]

03:24.395 --> 03:26.304
[Narrator]
Well, by spring time,

03:26.314 --> 03:28.222
they had made it official.

03:28.232 --> 03:30.146
Boy, let me tell you,

03:30.156 --> 03:32.066
that was some wedding.

03:32.076 --> 03:34.044
It was presided over
by Father Ken Gumbert,

03:34.054 --> 03:39.324
and half the Rhode Island
State Police Force was in attendance.

03:40.780 --> 03:44.860
- Congratulations, Charlie.
- Thank you, Captain.

03:45.643 --> 03:48.108
- [Engine Starts]
- [Cheering]

03:56.818 --> 03:58.818
[Laughing]

04:01.136 --> 04:03.136
- Ooh!
- All right.

04:06.123 --> 04:08.030
- Look what I got.
- Ooh!

04:08.040 --> 04:10.040
Whoo. Here we go.

04:11.658 --> 04:13.658
Ah.

04:17.423 --> 04:22.852
Oh, um, excuse me.
Do you people take checks?

04:22.929 --> 04:27.139
Say that again. Do we people
take checks? You mean, the black man?

04:27.149 --> 04:29.412
No, no, no, no, no.
God, no. Your company.

04:29.422 --> 04:32.617
Don't give me that backtracking
bullshit. That was a racist slur!

04:32.627 --> 04:34.824
No, it wasn't, really.
I-I would never--

04:34.834 --> 04:36.742
Tell you what!
I'll make it real easy for you.

04:36.752 --> 04:39.851
Why don't you just pay me
in cotton or a cartload of watermelons?

04:39.861 --> 04:42.890
Or how's about a couple
of them buckets of fried chicken?

04:42.900 --> 04:45.865
'Cause you know how we black people--
we just love fried chicken, Mr. Charlie.

04:45.875 --> 04:48.454
- Hey, no, come on now. Settle down.
- What's going on?

04:48.464 --> 04:51.299
This cat don't believe
a nigger knows how to cash a check.

04:51.309 --> 04:52.551
Ain't that about a bitch!

04:52.561 --> 04:55.754
Charlie, I don't wanna ever hear you
use the "N" word in this house.

04:55.764 --> 04:59.891
What? I-- I never said
anything remotely racist.

04:59.958 --> 05:03.318
- Oh, so it's
the little people thing then?

05:03.328 --> 05:03.564
No!

05:03.574 --> 05:06.440
You think just 'cause I'm small,
you can just push me around?

05:06.450 --> 05:08.369
Well, come on, my friend,
let's boogie.

05:08.379 --> 05:11.353
- I'm gonna give you a little
lesson in low center of gravity.

05:11.363 --> 05:11.602
What?

05:11.612 --> 05:13.904
- [Grunting]
- Hey, whoa, hey, stop it!

05:13.914 --> 05:16.782
Hey! Cut it--
Stop it now. Sir!

05:16.859 --> 05:19.371
Don't patronize me
with that "sir" crap.

05:19.381 --> 05:21.357
- Whoa, hey, those are illegal.
- [Gasping]

05:21.367 --> 05:24.186
Stop. Oh, God! Ow!

05:26.365 --> 05:29.203
- Oh, it's on now! It's on.
- Charlie!

05:29.213 --> 05:31.794
[Groaning]

05:31.871 --> 05:34.479
- Charlie, don't hit him!
- [Screaming]

05:34.489 --> 05:37.272
Charlie, Charlie, Charlie, stop it!
Charlie, stop it!

05:37.282 --> 05:41.522
Charlie, Charlie. Hey, hey, hey,
just let me handle this. Stop it!

05:41.532 --> 05:45.175
Excuse me, Mister, um,
"Jackson"--

05:45.252 --> 05:49.952
Uh-- Oh, stop it!
What-What-What is your first name?

05:50.019 --> 05:52.505
- It's Shonte.
- [Growling]

05:52.582 --> 05:57.311
Shonte, I'm-- I am--
I am so, so sorry. I apologize.

05:57.378 --> 06:01.146
Oh, come on, here.
Let me walk you to your car.

06:01.156 --> 06:04.150
I just don't have the patience for
people who judge books by their cover.

06:04.160 --> 06:06.077
And you shouldn't have to.

06:06.087 --> 06:09.656
Treating me like a dumbshit. I mean,
who does he think he's talking to?

06:09.666 --> 06:12.408
I'm a tenured professor
of molecular genetics over at Brown,

06:12.418 --> 06:15.241
- and I'm head
of the Boston chapter of MENSA.

06:15.251 --> 06:16.189
You're kidding?

06:16.199 --> 06:21.599
No. I'm just driving this limo
as a sociologic experiment, that's it.

06:21.609 --> 06:25.879
- But MENSA? I'm president
of the Providence chapter.

06:25.889 --> 06:26.845
No kidding.

06:26.855 --> 06:28.855
[Chuckling]

06:32.841 --> 06:36.870
[Narrator]Just when Charlie thought
life couldn't get any sweeter,

06:36.880 --> 06:40.965
old Mr. Stork dropped in
to pay him and Layla a visit.

06:40.975 --> 06:45.283
- [Groaning, Screaming]
- It's a boy!

06:45.359 --> 06:48.142
Oh, boy, oy, oy.

06:50.866 --> 06:52.866
Wow!

06:53.744 --> 06:58.530
He's so-- Wow!

06:58.607 --> 07:02.607
- [Panting]
- Huh? What?

07:02.674 --> 07:05.789
- [Screaming]
- Whoa, oh, my God, we're in luck.

07:05.799 --> 07:06.923
He's got company!

07:06.933 --> 07:10.060
- [Both Screaming]
- Push! Push!

07:11.346 --> 07:13.514
[Narrator]
Charlie loved those boys so much,

07:13.524 --> 07:15.566
he just couldn't face
the truth.

07:15.576 --> 07:20.676
And so he went on with his life,
as if everything was normal.

07:21.946 --> 07:24.756
Hey, Finneran.
Hey, Buddy.

07:24.823 --> 07:27.557
- Hey! Hope you brought
your appetite with ya.

07:27.567 --> 07:28.171
Oh, I did.

07:28.181 --> 07:30.377
- Ahh!
- Charlie, your kids look great.

07:30.387 --> 07:33.447
- Yeah, don't they? Thanks.
- Uh-huh.

07:36.124 --> 07:38.124
- Charlie,
- [Screams]

07:38.167 --> 07:40.306
just between you and me,

07:40.382 --> 07:44.430
did you ever notice that your kids have
sort of a year-round tan?

07:44.440 --> 07:47.030
Yeah, well, uh--

07:47.097 --> 07:49.744
- My great grandmother's half Italian.
- Half Italian?

07:49.754 --> 07:51.668
Oh, yeah.

07:51.678 --> 07:55.031
Well, that's probably why
the water beads off their hair, huh?

07:55.041 --> 07:57.821
[Sighs]
Yeah, so?

07:57.888 --> 08:01.836
- I mean, a lot of people have
different kind of hair.

08:01.846 --> 08:02.512
Oh, yeah.

08:02.522 --> 08:05.303
I mean, what are you--
what are you-- what are you getting at?

08:05.313 --> 08:08.543
No, no, I'm just saying is--
You know--

08:08.575 --> 08:10.579
Come on, Charlie,
goddamn it!

08:10.589 --> 08:13.016
Those kids' dicks are bigger
than them sausages.

08:13.026 --> 08:15.251
Knock it off, Finneran. Those are
my children you're talking about.

08:15.261 --> 08:17.930
- I've been meaning
to ask you about that.

08:17.940 --> 08:18.522
Finneran!

08:18.532 --> 08:20.997
Get over here.
It's your turn.

08:25.669 --> 08:28.537
Charlie, don't mind me.

08:28.614 --> 08:30.551
It's j-just the beer talking,
you know? Whoo!

08:30.561 --> 08:33.534
Hmm. Sure.

08:40.327 --> 08:45.726
[Charlie] There's something powerful
bubbling up inside me, Father,

08:45.736 --> 08:48.672
and I'm afraid that someday,

08:51.338 --> 08:54.984
if I don't do something,
I'm gonna explode.

08:55.051 --> 08:59.560
[Sighs] Where does this rage
come from, my son?

08:59.627 --> 09:03.886
I don't know.
It's a lot of things, really.

09:03.953 --> 09:06.082
Take my wife, for example.

09:06.092 --> 09:08.366
I love her like no other,

09:08.433 --> 09:12.001
but part of me suspects
that she may be having an affair.

09:12.011 --> 09:15.330
And I'm-I'm probably
just being paranoid here,

09:15.340 --> 09:17.613
but I get the feeling...

09:17.680 --> 09:22.185
that the entire town is
laughing at me behind my back.

09:23.379 --> 09:26.727
Charlie, that you?

09:26.804 --> 09:30.600
[Narrator] Eventually,
Charlie's worst fears were realized.

09:30.610 --> 09:35.944
I'm so sorry, Charlie.
Really, I am.

09:36.021 --> 09:40.971
But I have to do this.
I found my soul mate.

09:41.048 --> 09:43.048
But...
[Exhales]

09:43.062 --> 09:45.451
I thought I was your soul mate.

09:45.461 --> 09:47.461
Tsk. Oh.

09:47.513 --> 09:50.362
Come on, legs.
Let's roll, baby.

09:52.185 --> 09:54.832
I don't know what to say.

09:54.908 --> 09:59.073
I guess the heart just wants
what the heart wants.

10:00.348 --> 10:02.348
Bye, Charlie.

10:04.089 --> 10:05.997
But you said
you'd eat whale blubber.

10:06.007 --> 10:11.872
Oh, she'll be eating blubber,
all right, just as soon as I free willy.

10:19.677 --> 10:22.497
- [Groaning]
- [Engine Starts]

10:25.155 --> 10:29.912
[Narrator] It's funny how a man
reacts when his heart gets broken.

10:29.922 --> 10:32.501
Some break down
and cry like a baby.

10:32.511 --> 10:35.610
Others, they take out an Uzi
and climb a clock tower.

10:35.620 --> 10:38.746
But Charlie Bailey gates
didn't seem to react at all.

10:38.756 --> 10:40.670
He just swallowed hard,

10:40.680 --> 10:44.539
felt that slab of heartache
slide over the lump in this throat,

10:44.549 --> 10:46.881
and he locked it all away.

10:51.590 --> 10:53.623
As you can imagine,
it wasn't easy...

10:53.633 --> 10:57.049
for little Jamaal,
Lee Harvey and Shonte Junior...

10:57.059 --> 10:58.977
growing up without a mom,

10:58.987 --> 11:04.377
but Charlie made that little house into
a big old home, and the boys flourished.

11:04.387 --> 11:07.418
Let me tell you,
they were smart ones.

11:07.428 --> 11:11.198
- What are you buildin', fellas?
- An airplane, Daddy.

11:11.208 --> 11:13.502
[Imitating Airplane Engine]

11:13.512 --> 11:17.059
- [Laughing]
- Bye-bye!

11:17.127 --> 11:20.406
- [All] Bye, Daddy!
- Have a good time at work!

11:20.416 --> 11:22.416
Bye, Daddy!

11:23.650 --> 11:25.562
Love you, Daddy!

11:25.572 --> 11:28.148
Where he can't hide

11:28.225 --> 11:31.803
-From himself
- No. No!

11:31.871 --> 11:37.213
Hey! Stop it! Jamaal, you're
in a lot of trouble! Get off that!

11:37.280 --> 11:39.575
Don't you take off in that!

11:41.030 --> 11:44.174
-How many seas
must a white dove sail

11:44.184 --> 11:45.463
Shonte Junior,

11:45.473 --> 11:48.253
How can you keep eatin' that crap
and never gain weight?

11:48.263 --> 11:51.486
- I don't know. Just lucky, I guess.
- [Chuckles]

11:51.496 --> 11:53.885
How many times

11:53.962 --> 11:57.035
-Must the cannonballs fly
- Do you believe his voice?

11:57.045 --> 11:58.104
That's Gomer Pyle!

11:58.114 --> 12:01.665
Before they're
forever banned

12:01.732 --> 12:04.247
- The answer, my friend
- Daddy, can we watch

12:04.257 --> 12:05.626
Richard Pryor on H.B.O.?

12:05.636 --> 12:07.842
-Is blowing in the wind
- Richard Pryor?

12:07.852 --> 12:11.018
- Please.
- Okay.

12:13.357 --> 12:14.940
In Africa, though,
I go out

12:14.950 --> 12:16.226
in the country. Whoo!

12:16.236 --> 12:20.197
You see some lions and shit.
I'm talkin' about real lions,

12:20.207 --> 12:23.842
not them kind you be
fuckin' with in the zoo.

12:23.852 --> 12:28.102
You fuck with the lions,
"Hey, lion, motherfucker!"

12:28.591 --> 12:31.679
Be throwin' shit at it.
Lion be, "Uh-oh, oh!"

12:31.689 --> 12:34.630
[Narrator] As they have
a way of doing, the years

12:34.640 --> 12:36.294
passed some what regularly.

12:36.304 --> 12:40.170
And the boys, well,
they came into their own.

12:40.237 --> 12:44.486
...is make her
toss my salad!

12:44.563 --> 12:47.527
The guy's like, "Toss my salad?
W-Well, what's that?"

12:47.537 --> 12:49.580
Yeah, well,
having your salad tossed...

12:49.590 --> 12:53.482
means having your asshole
eaten out with jelly or syrup.

12:53.492 --> 12:55.492
I prefer syrup.

12:56.371 --> 12:58.827
He's a funny motherfucker.

13:03.221 --> 13:06.318
[Narrator] Although Charlie's
police work had started to suffer,

13:06.328 --> 13:08.237
the kids were doing great.

13:08.247 --> 13:13.513
Damn! I can't figure out the atomic
mass of this motherfuckin' deuteron.

13:13.523 --> 13:15.977
Shit, man,
that shit's simple.

13:15.987 --> 13:19.373
- Look. Tell me this, tell me this.
- What, what?

13:19.383 --> 13:23.441
- What's a deuteron made up of?
- Duh, a proton and a neutron.

13:23.451 --> 13:27.509
Then what's this motherfuckin' electron
doin' right there?

13:27.519 --> 13:31.182
- Shit, I don't know.
- Well, get it outta there then!

13:31.192 --> 13:33.671
Okay, so you sayin' I add up
the atomic masses of the proton

13:33.681 --> 13:34.645
and the neutron, right?

13:34.655 --> 13:36.254
- Mm-hmm.
- I sees that, but what do I do

13:36.264 --> 13:37.302
with the goddamn electron?

13:37.312 --> 13:39.220
Can I bring it over here?

13:39.230 --> 13:41.552
Enrico Fermi would roll over
in his motherfuckin' grave

13:41.562 --> 13:42.809
if he heard that stupid shit.

13:42.819 --> 13:45.427
I mean, he'd just turn over ass up
in your face. He wouldn't give a fuck.

13:45.437 --> 13:47.442
Man,Jamaal, man,
just cut my man some slack, dog.

13:47.452 --> 13:48.376
Look here, I'm just try
in'

13:48.386 --> 13:49.561
to help him save face, all right?

13:49.571 --> 13:52.467
He keep askin' questions like that,
motherfuckers gonna think he's stupid.

13:52.477 --> 13:54.387
- I ain't stupid.
- Mornin', fellas.

13:54.397 --> 13:57.236
- Oh, hey, Dad.
- Hey, Pops, how you doin', man?

13:57.246 --> 14:00.565
- What's all the commotion down here?
-Just school shit and shit.

14:00.575 --> 14:03.331
- How's my little guy doin'?
- Strugglin'. This quantum

14:03.341 --> 14:04.411
physics is confusing.

14:04.421 --> 14:07.544
- If I don't buckle down,
I'm gonna get myself another B-plus.

14:07.554 --> 14:08.573
Oh, that'd be whack.

14:08.583 --> 14:12.315
Man, he so fuckin' dumb,
he think calculus is a goddamn emperor.

14:12.325 --> 14:15.388
- Give it up, dog.
- Well, you think polypeptide's

14:15.398 --> 14:17.082
a motherfuckin' toothpaste.

14:17.092 --> 14:21.725
Oh, I gotta get outta here.
I don't want to have to bust a cap.

14:21.735 --> 14:24.124
Kisses.

14:24.201 --> 14:26.466
Mm, Daddy.

14:26.533 --> 14:27.694
- See ya later.
- Love

14:27.704 --> 14:28.478
ya! All right.

14:28.488 --> 14:33.409
[Narrator] Yeah, Charlie was gettin'
a lot of respect inside the house,

14:33.419 --> 14:37.860
but outside--
well, that was another story.

14:41.639 --> 14:43.653
Mornin', Ed.

14:43.720 --> 14:46.435
Charlie.

14:46.502 --> 14:49.055
Say, Ed, did you see
where my paper went today?

14:49.065 --> 14:52.125
Uh, the wife's got it
in the shitter.

14:53.323 --> 14:57.984
Well, could you tell her to throw it
on the porch when she's done?

14:57.994 --> 15:00.204
Can't you get one at work?

15:04.173 --> 15:07.896
Yeah, I
...suppose I could.

15:07.906 --> 15:09.905
You betcha.

15:19.320 --> 15:22.255
I'd like that

15:22.322 --> 15:26.696
If we could cycle
down some lane

15:26.772 --> 15:30.322
I'd like that

15:30.389 --> 15:34.062
If we could ride
into the rain

15:34.129 --> 15:36.241
No mess getting wet

15:36.308 --> 15:38.764
I'd be your Albert

15:38.840 --> 15:42.189
If you'd be Victoria

15:42.265 --> 15:45.391
Ha, ha
We'd laugh because

15:45.468 --> 15:50.073
Each drop would make me
grow up really high

15:50.140 --> 15:54.102
Really high like a really high thing
say a sun flower

15:54.112 --> 15:56.913
- Hey, Charlie.
- Hey, George, Herb.

15:56.923 --> 15:59.089
- Hi, Charlie.
- How do, fellas?

15:59.099 --> 16:01.239
- Hi, Charlie.
- Listen, Dick, I was--

16:01.249 --> 16:05.105
Hey, guys, check out
the rack on this one.

16:05.182 --> 16:07.182
Whoa!

16:07.235 --> 16:09.488
Oh, yeah,
that's what daddy likes.

16:09.498 --> 16:11.801
It looks like a dead heat
in a zeppelin race.

16:11.811 --> 16:15.158
- Yeah, a couple of Hindenburgs, huh?
- Oh, the humanity!

16:15.168 --> 16:18.568
Come on, guys, take it easy.
She's a mom.

16:21.537 --> 16:24.021
[Laughing]

16:25.248 --> 16:27.248
"She's a mom."

16:29.345 --> 16:32.660
- She's not my mom!
- She's a yummy mom.

16:35.781 --> 16:38.331
- You kill me!
- "She's a mom."

16:43.877 --> 16:48.578
Sure, that is good.
Oh.

16:48.646 --> 16:52.347
Listen, uh, Dick, I'm sorry,
uh, to bother you like this,

16:52.357 --> 16:57.181
but, uh, uh, your-your-your car
is gonna have to be moved.

16:57.191 --> 16:59.772
[Chuckling]
Yeah, sure, Charlie, okay.

16:59.782 --> 17:04.060
I should be done here
in another ten or fifteen minutes.

17:04.069 --> 17:06.880
You know,
I hate to be a stickler, Dick,

17:06.890 --> 17:09.086
but, uh, the law states that you can't
park in one place for more than an hour,

17:09.096 --> 17:12.550
and you've been there for--

17:12.617 --> 17:14.689
goin' on three days now.

17:16.079 --> 17:20.040
All right, all right,
the law's the law.

17:20.108 --> 17:24.358
Park it behind the grocery store,
will ya, Charlie?

17:26.708 --> 17:29.040
Yeah, sure.

17:30.804 --> 17:34.055
- This one?
