34:45.985 --> 34:49.641
So I smoked some pot.
What is that, a crime?

34:50.523 --> 34:52.440
Uh-huh.

34:52.451 --> 34:55.059
As is being an accessory
to bribery, embezzlement,

34:55.069 --> 34:56.978
tax evasion
and racketeering.

34:56.987 --> 35:01.263
- What are you talking about?
- Does the name Dickie Thurman

35:01.273 --> 35:02.140
ring a bell?

35:02.150 --> 35:04.606
His company,
Cedar Creek Limited,

35:04.616 --> 35:07.349
has been under a sealed
grand jury investigation for 18 months.

35:07.359 --> 35:11.225
How does that make me an accessory?
I laid some sod on Dickie's golf course.

35:11.235 --> 35:11.387
So?

35:11.397 --> 35:15.741
Tell me this--a big operation like
the Cedar Creek Country Club--

35:15.751 --> 35:18.362
how'd you get the job
as the head greens keeper?

35:18.372 --> 35:22.879
By default. This guy,
Tedeschi or Tedescho,

35:22.947 --> 35:24.862
he was hired before me,
but he died.

35:24.872 --> 35:27.167
Heart problem or something.

35:28.904 --> 35:30.754
[Narrator]
The feds believed that Irene knew...

35:30.764 --> 35:32.673
more than
she thought she knew,

35:32.683 --> 35:34.715
and her life was in danger.

35:34.725 --> 35:38.466
They explained that everything had
been happening right under her nose--

35:38.476 --> 35:42.275
payoffs of government agencies, threats
towards those who stood in the way,

35:42.285 --> 35:44.932
and her predecessor's
heart attack?

35:44.942 --> 35:48.126
Well, that was just
cold blooded murder.

35:48.136 --> 35:50.477
Oh, man.

35:58.410 --> 36:00.932
Can you excuse me?

36:17.680 --> 36:20.713
Pizza kid.

36:22.708 --> 36:26.122
- How much?
- Uh, that comes to 13.95.

36:26.199 --> 36:28.199
[Grunts]

36:40.693 --> 36:42.693
[Grunts]

36:50.008 --> 36:52.347
Oh, son of a bitch!

37:00.158 --> 37:02.158
[Car Departing]

37:03.293 --> 37:05.293
[Panting]

37:08.511 --> 37:10.966
[Narrator] Well, it was a good thing
Charlie had told her...

37:10.976 --> 37:15.601
he was staying at the Chuck E. Cheese
Lodge and Miniature Golf Resort.

37:15.611 --> 37:17.202
Charlie?

37:17.212 --> 37:21.586
Irene finagled a key
from the front desk and let her self in.

37:21.596 --> 37:23.596
Charlie.

37:25.308 --> 37:27.308
[Snoring]

37:33.127 --> 37:37.146
- Charlie, what's going on here?
- Hmm? Irene?

37:37.223 --> 37:39.745
Oh! Oh, uh, uh--
[Chuckling]

37:39.812 --> 37:43.994
Irene, I was just, um--
I was gonna, um, study your file...

37:44.004 --> 37:46.824
and, uh, try to find
a loophole.

37:48.905 --> 37:52.129
Did your lips get as chapped
as mine on the ride down?

37:52.139 --> 37:54.075
Nevermind!
I need your help.

37:54.085 --> 37:56.828
There was a shootout down at the thing,
and the agents are dead.

37:56.838 --> 38:00.129
- Dead?
- Yeah, they were after me, Charlie.

38:00.139 --> 38:00.474
Oh, God. See, this is Dickie's work.
I know it.

38:00.484 --> 38:04.394
Oh, God. See, this is Dickie's work.
I know it.

38:07.085 --> 38:11.266
- So what are you gonna do?
- We'll call the police.

38:11.276 --> 38:13.185
What?
No, you can't do that.

38:13.195 --> 38:16.388
Dickie has those guys in his
back pocket. That's why I came to you.

38:16.398 --> 38:18.402
- How-- Wha-- How do you--
- Oh!

38:18.412 --> 38:21.607
Hey, this is serious shit!
You don't--

38:21.674 --> 38:24.130
[Sighs]
I'm outta here.

38:24.207 --> 38:26.572
Hey, wait. No, don't do that!
Come on, hold on!

38:26.582 --> 38:28.485
Just let me think for a second, okay?

38:28.495 --> 38:31.976
Think someplace else, Charlie. This is
the first place they're gonna look.

38:31.986 --> 38:33.986
Damn it!

38:41.137 --> 38:44.962
- So where are we going, anyway?
- You'll see!

38:46.001 --> 38:48.686
[Narrator]
Well, they went on the lam for a bit,

38:48.696 --> 38:51.717
- and then Charlie made
a couple of phone calls.

38:51.727 --> 38:53.727
[Barking]

39:00.755 --> 39:03.411
Irene, take it easy now.

39:03.479 --> 39:06.413
- Charlie?
- Don't worry. I'll take care of it.

39:06.423 --> 39:09.972
- Hey.
- Good work, Bailey gates.

39:10.039 --> 39:11.968
- Thanks.
- I'm sorry I had to meet you

39:11.978 --> 39:13.043
all the way out here.

39:13.053 --> 39:14.959
No, that's okay.
It's just as well.

39:14.969 --> 39:17.454
Poor gal's a little paranoid.
My kids are like that.

39:17.464 --> 39:19.487
Somewhere along the line,
they just get this idea that

39:19.497 --> 39:20.524
the cops are the bad guys--

39:20.534 --> 39:24.659
[Grunting, Gasping]

39:27.106 --> 39:30.960
Listen, I don't know what's going on,
and I didn't tell the feds anything.

39:30.970 --> 39:34.587
Dickie told me
you were street smart, huh?

39:34.654 --> 39:36.563
Why the hell would you
run back to this idiot?

39:36.573 --> 39:38.913
[Drums]

39:42.146 --> 39:45.886
Drop the gun, moron.
You're being videotaped.

39:48.133 --> 39:52.890
- What are you talkin' about?
- There's a camera on my bike.

39:52.900 --> 39:56.730
- [Irene Screams]
- Hard to hit a moving target,

39:56.740 --> 39:58.740
isn't it?

39:59.874 --> 40:02.914
- [Grunting]
- [Groaning]

40:10.819 --> 40:12.958
[Panting]

40:13.034 --> 40:15.232
Score. Good move.

40:15.309 --> 40:18.119
Get in the car.

40:18.186 --> 40:22.606
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on.

40:23.595 --> 40:27.230
[Irene] Would you mind telling me what
the hell you were thinking back there?

40:27.240 --> 40:29.955
Calling that cop
was unbelievably stupid.

40:29.965 --> 40:33.130
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

40:33.197 --> 40:35.297
Tweak the high end
of your emotional E.Q, sweetbeak.

40:35.307 --> 40:37.341
The funky chicken
was Charlie's dance.

40:37.351 --> 40:40.997
I'm a tango man myself.

40:41.074 --> 40:44.009
[Tango]

40:44.076 --> 40:45.988
[Snarls]

40:45.998 --> 40:50.053
[Narrator]As you can imagine,
there was some explaining to do.

40:50.063 --> 40:53.419
So, Hank, [Clears Throat]
as he called himself,

40:53.429 --> 40:57.515
found a quiet spot
and spelled out the whole darn mess.

40:57.525 --> 41:00.938
Okay, so what you're saying is
that you're not Charlie.

41:00.948 --> 41:03.693
Come on, you've seen Charlie in action.
The guy's like origami.

41:03.703 --> 41:07.051
He folds under pressure.
When the big game's on the line,

41:07.061 --> 41:08.614
he's busy ridin' the pine.

41:08.624 --> 41:11.259
Okay, wait, wait.
Can you just--

41:15.923 --> 41:18.638
It's simple.

41:18.705 --> 41:20.939
Charlie's the mouse
that got you into the maze.

41:20.949 --> 41:23.760
I'm the rat who knows
how to find the cheese.

41:23.770 --> 41:27.214
The name's Hank--
Hank Evans.

41:27.291 --> 41:30.801
- For little girls
- So it's true.

41:30.869 --> 41:34.321
- Charlie is a schizo.
- I wouldn't know.

41:34.389 --> 41:37.900
I stay outta his business,
he stays outta mine.

41:37.910 --> 41:39.910
Look.

41:42.619 --> 41:44.756
Just because I rock
doesn't mean I'm made of stone.

41:44.766 --> 41:47.099
I feel your fear.

41:47.165 --> 41:51.330
It's comin' through like static
on my heart radio.

41:52.673 --> 41:55.003
Hank? Hank.

41:56.030 --> 41:59.060
I really, really
appreciate your help,

41:59.070 --> 42:01.938
but is there anyway
that maybe we could get...

42:01.948 --> 42:05.334
Charlie back out here
for a little huddle?

42:05.344 --> 42:07.344
No problem.

42:07.397 --> 42:09.207
While you're at it,
climb that pole over there and

42:09.217 --> 42:10.361
take a piss on the power lines.

42:10.371 --> 42:14.360
Look, I'm not here to twist your
niblets. I'm here to save your life.

42:14.370 --> 42:19.425
But if I'm gonna do that,
I'll need total "uninanonynymity."

42:22.946 --> 42:24.859
Okay.

42:24.869 --> 42:29.787
- Sound good, candypants?
- Hank, don't call me that.

42:41.000 --> 42:44.097
Man, how the hell
can they call Pluto a planet?

42:44.107 --> 42:46.178
What motherfuckin' planet
has an elliptical orbit?

42:46.188 --> 42:48.098
Man, this shit
don't make no sense.

42:48.108 --> 42:53.028
Motherfucker! That motherfucker Vince
Foster was murdered! I told you!

42:53.038 --> 42:56.645
Will you quit hackin' into
them goddamn Pentagon files?

42:56.655 --> 42:59.682
Ain't no nevermind who them
crooked politicians be killin'.

42:59.692 --> 43:00.835
Just do your studyin'.

43:00.845 --> 43:03.159
- Man, what did Daddy tell you
about snoopin', huh?

43:03.169 --> 43:03.907
Shit, yeah, man.

43:03.917 --> 43:06.034
You keep fuckin' around,
you gonna get that scholarship

43:06.044 --> 43:07.139
to Yale taken away from you.

43:07.149 --> 43:10.342
Be stuck up there at Stanford with them
goddamn sling-blade motherfuckers.

43:10.352 --> 43:12.265
[Laughing]

43:12.275 --> 43:14.773
Shit, motherfucker,
you be lucky to get accepted to Duke

43:14.783 --> 43:16.098
gettin' a 1430 on your S.A.T.

43:16.108 --> 43:18.534
- Motherfucker, you know I had the flu.
- The flu, my ass.

43:18.544 --> 43:21.479
You had a motherfuckin' aneurysm
gettin' a 1430.

43:21.489 --> 43:23.623
- Aneurysm?
Man, you talkin' some shit now.

43:23.633 --> 43:24.138
[Knocking]

43:24.148 --> 43:27.495
Now you see, man? That's probably
one of them Ivy League sum bitches now.

43:27.505 --> 43:29.001
- Get your big-ass head up
and get the door, man.

43:29.011 --> 43:29.412
Get the door.

43:29.422 --> 43:30.660
- Don't fuck with my shit.
- Get outta the way.

43:30.670 --> 43:31.342
Gimme some of them chips.

43:31.352 --> 43:33.836
[Laughing]
Hey, Captain.

43:33.913 --> 43:37.422
- Fellas.
- What the fuck is goin' on, man?

43:37.432 --> 43:40.847
- This is Agent Anicelli.
- Gentlemen.

43:40.914 --> 43:43.791
- What's happenin', Captain?
- We've got a problem.

43:43.801 --> 43:46.104
Pack your bags.

43:51.707 --> 43:53.614
- We're locked and loaded.
- Great.

43:53.624 --> 43:57.455
- Got enough stuff
to hold us over for 72 hours.

43:57.465 --> 43:59.465
[Men Laughing]

44:09.595 --> 44:11.927
Well, fuck my ozone.

44:14.431 --> 44:16.666
[Drums]

44:26.404 --> 44:30.394
Nyah, nyah, nyah-nyah-nyah
We're gonna rock you

44:37.828 --> 44:39.828
Hey, ringworm.

44:42.566 --> 44:47.035
Yeah, I'm talkin' to you,
you toxic waste of life.

44:47.103 --> 44:50.297
You gonna pick up that butt, or do I
have to glue it to the end of my shoe...

44:50.307 --> 44:52.378
and stick it in your
big, fat, pimply A-hole?

44:52.388 --> 44:56.379
Hey, man, take it easy.
It's just a cigarette.

44:56.456 --> 45:00.416
Oh, yeah?
Well, this is just a fist.

45:00.484 --> 45:03.746
But when I start throwing it around,
it can leave one hell of a mess.

45:03.756 --> 45:05.761
Let's dance.

45:22.663 --> 45:25.933
Hey, hey!
[Groaning]

45:26.002 --> 45:29.062
Let's kick the shit
outta this crazy asshole.

45:29.072 --> 45:32.199
Wait, wait. Wait!
He's a schizo!

45:32.265 --> 45:34.815
What the hell's wrong
with him?

45:37.042 --> 45:39.181
What happened, anyway?

45:39.248 --> 45:43.746
[Narrator] Yeah, Charlie was taking a
few lumps on account of Hank's behavior.

45:43.756 --> 45:49.791
But, save for a little blood in the
urine, he was no worse for the wear.

45:50.261 --> 45:52.265
I'm sorry you had to meet Hank,
Miss Waters.

45:52.275 --> 45:57.714
I thought I was bad.
That guy has some serious problems.

45:58.741 --> 46:00.741
He did save our lives.

46:02.903 --> 46:05.196
Anyway, Hank had
a pretty good idea.

46:05.206 --> 46:07.181
- He thinks that maybe--
- Oh, and you're gonna listen to Hank?

46:07.191 --> 46:10.184
Come on!Look what he did tome.
I mean, what are you thinkin'?

46:10.194 --> 46:12.744
He's out of control, this guy.

46:12.793 --> 46:15.307
You know what I think
we should do?

46:15.317 --> 46:17.067
I think we should find
another department

46:17.077 --> 46:18.384
and tell them the whole story.

46:18.394 --> 46:23.579
Not smart, Charlie. We don't know
how far Dickie's reach goes.

46:24.602 --> 46:26.674
Well, then, you know what?

46:26.684 --> 46:31.087
I think it's time to call the best damn
law enforcement agency in the country:

46:31.097 --> 46:33.265
the Rhode Island State Troopers!

46:33.275 --> 46:37.494
Do you really think the feds don't have
some guy up there now bugging calls?

46:37.504 --> 46:40.017
They'd be on us
in ten minutes.

46:40.027 --> 46:42.837
And they're the ones that almost
got me killed in the first place.

46:42.847 --> 46:47.154
Okay. What was
the genius's big plan?

46:47.231 --> 46:50.674
He thinks that we should find a cabin
and hide out for a while.

46:50.684 --> 46:53.139
Oh, yeah?
What about water? What about food?

46:53.149 --> 46:56.974
He already got supplies.
They're in the trunk.

47:05.600 --> 47:08.490
- These are the supplies?
- Mm-hmm.

47:10.848 --> 47:14.263
Well, he had a plan, all right.
[Sucking Sounds]

47:14.273 --> 47:17.093
That's it?
That's all he got?

47:17.160 --> 47:19.969
Oh, no, there's more.

47:20.036 --> 47:24.067
A rope, a shovel,

47:24.134 --> 47:26.954
bag of lime
and some lawn darts.

47:39.530 --> 47:41.362
- and the kidnapping
of one Irene P. Waters.

47:41.372 --> 47:42.052
That's bullshit!

47:42.062 --> 47:44.023
My daddy ain't killed nobody,
and he sure as shit ain't

47:44.033 --> 47:45.121
kidnapped no skinny-ass bitch!

47:45.131 --> 47:47.398
Your dad's sick, mentally.
He's had some sort of breakdown.

47:47.408 --> 47:48.421
That's what we understand.

47:48.431 --> 47:51.808
The important thing is we find him, so
nobody else gets hurt, himself included.

47:51.818 --> 47:53.736
Come on, man,
nobody's gonna get hurt.

47:53.746 --> 47:56.163
Hell, yeah. Our daddy wouldn't hurt
a motherfuckin' fly.

47:56.173 --> 47:58.465
No, he goes after bigger game.

47:58.475 --> 48:01.449
We just got a report he put six bullets
into a prize cow's head.

48:01.459 --> 48:04.009
Poor thing's lucky
to be alive.

48:06.063 --> 48:09.285
Okay, look, let's say he does
have a problem-- which he don't.

48:09.295 --> 48:11.305
- He's been taking pills
to get rid of it, anyway.

48:11.315 --> 48:12.585
He left his pills in the hotel.

48:12.595 --> 48:14.504
- Damn.
- That's where he left his sanity.

48:14.514 --> 48:17.736
I've seen it first hand.
The guy's nuttier than squirrel turds.

48:17.746 --> 48:22.503
L-L-Look. One thing
I don't understand, Lieutenant.

48:22.580 --> 48:24.361
If my daddy's
such a scary-ass motherfucker,

48:24.371 --> 48:25.612
why'd you go by yourself, huh?

48:25.622 --> 48:28.026
Yeah, who the fuck are you,
Sergeant York, tryin' to take on

48:28.036 --> 48:29.131
the Germans your damn self?

48:29.141 --> 48:32.296
Your father's a police officer,
and he asked me to come alone.

48:32.306 --> 48:34.063
How was I to know he's a nut case?

48:34.073 --> 48:35.788
- Man, our daddy ain't
no fuckin' nut case.

48:35.798 --> 48:36.364
He may have...

48:36.374 --> 48:39.723
advanced delusionary schizophrenia
with involuntary narcissistic rage,

48:39.733 --> 48:42.283
but he is
a very gentle person!

48:42.361 --> 48:43.831
-[Punk On Radio]
- Motherfuckin' robot

48:43.841 --> 48:44.596
Motherfuckin' robot

48:44.606 --> 48:46.773
[Continues]

48:46.840 --> 48:48.840
[Radio Off]

48:50.333 --> 48:53.708
Whoa, whoa, whoa, what's the fuzz?
Tell me what's a-happening.

48:53.718 --> 48:57.868
Stay away from me, Hank!
I know what you had planned.

48:57.878 --> 49:00.271
I saw your so-called supplies.

49:00.281 --> 49:02.802
Oh, that?

49:04.443 --> 49:07.378
I wasn't gonna just
ram it home, you know.

49:07.388 --> 49:09.594
I was gonna lube it up...

49:09.661 --> 49:13.171
and ease it in there
inch by inch, like a gentleman.

49:13.181 --> 49:16.788
I was talking about
the shovel and the lime.

49:16.798 --> 49:19.140
Shovel and lime?

49:19.197 --> 49:21.988
[Chuckling]

49:22.046 --> 49:24.046
[Laughing]

49:25.412 --> 49:28.155
[Sighs]
Thank you.

49:28.223 --> 49:30.160
- I haven't laughed like that
in a long time.

49:30.170 --> 49:30.869
What's so funny?

49:30.879 --> 49:34.399
- We're drivin' a hot carriage.
- So?

49:34.466 --> 49:36.759
That stuff belongs
to the bad cop.

49:36.769 --> 49:39.196
You think he was gonna take
our dead bodies down to the station?

49:39.206 --> 49:41.988
Oh.

49:47.686 --> 49:50.621
[Narrator] Irene decided
they should go back to Rhode Island,

49:50.631 --> 49:53.316
but Hank had an idea first.

49:53.384 --> 49:56.348
- Are you sure about this?
- Are you kiddin'?

49:56.358 --> 49:59.551
Every oinker east of the Mississippi
will be looking for this sled.

49:59.561 --> 50:03.340
Safer to go mass transit.
Ready? On nine.

50:03.398 --> 50:05.318
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine.

50:05.328 --> 50:09.222
I can't keep up
with you no more

50:09.289 --> 50:14.046
And you treat me
like it's a sin

50:14.123 --> 50:19.005
For you to let me in

50:19.139 --> 50:22.880
Well, they won't be
tracking us in that car.

50:22.948 --> 50:25.115
- Thanks for the kudos.
- Sure.

50:25.125 --> 50:27.994
- Glad we're finally on the same page.
- Me too.

50:28.004 --> 50:31.170
Whoa! You okay?

50:31.237 --> 50:33.237
Yes, I'm fine.

50:34.537 --> 50:37.596
[Sighs]
Thought you were goin' over the edge.

50:37.606 --> 50:39.606
Thank you.

50:43.236 --> 50:46.596
- You know, I think you're
a very special unit.

50:46.606 --> 50:47.553
That's sweet.

50:47.563 --> 50:49.951
I hope we can get
to know each other better.

50:49.961 --> 50:52.387
Yeah, me too.

50:52.454 --> 50:54.469
Do you swallow?

50:58.153 --> 51:01.223
I get it.
We'll go slow.

51:06.057 --> 51:08.484
- Hey!
- Yes?

51:09.904 --> 51:13.635
You didn't happen to pick up
a wallet on the dash, did ya?

51:13.645 --> 51:15.716
You're kidding, right?

51:16.906 --> 51:18.825
[Exhales]

51:18.835 --> 51:21.414
So, what's your tale, Mother Goose?
Where you from?

51:21.424 --> 51:23.424
Oh, all over.

51:23.439 --> 51:26.537
Omnipresence--
I like that in a woman.

51:26.547 --> 51:29.799
I'm originally from Texas.
Middle-class neighborhood.

51:29.809 --> 51:32.197
But after high school, I moved
to New York, 'cause I had this thing--

51:32.207 --> 51:35.112
Let me guess. Everybody in town
told you you were easy on the eyes,

51:35.122 --> 51:36.878
so you decided
to become a supermodel.

51:36.888 --> 51:39.400
When you got to the Big Apple,
they treated you like the worm.

51:39.410 --> 51:41.895
So you packed on a few pounds
and started calling yourself an actress.

51:41.905 --> 51:43.905
- Uh, no.
- Shh!

51:43.958 --> 51:46.192
Unfortunately,
you can't get far without talent,

51:46.202 --> 51:48.112
and after a while the only bright lights
you saw were the ones...

51:48.122 --> 51:50.508
that hit you in the face
when you opened the fridge.

51:50.518 --> 51:52.946
That's when you got a boob job, started
hanging around on the Upper East Side,

51:52.956 --> 51:54.537
looking for a rich, old man
with a bum ticker...

51:54.547 --> 51:59.055
and waved a white flag
in the face of your own self-loathing.

51:59.065 --> 52:01.521
How's my aim?

52:01.588 --> 52:04.878
I never went to New York City.
I went upstate to Cornell.

52:04.888 --> 52:07.602
And then I got my master's
in turf management at U-Mass.

52:07.612 --> 52:09.934
And then I became
